1
00:00:04,200 --> 00:00:05,180
- Hey, guys. - Hey.

2
00:00:05,230 --> 00:00:06,600
- Hi. - Hey.

3
00:00:07,040 --> 00:00:09,060
We need to talk about something.

4
00:00:09,110 --> 00:00:10,430
Yeah. We don't feel like

5
00:00:10,480 --> 00:00:12,130
we can host Thanksgiving this year.

6
00:00:12,310 --> 00:00:14,070
- What... - Are you kidding?

7
00:00:14,120 --> 00:00:17,120
Well, it's just with work and the stress of adoption...

8
00:00:17,170 --> 00:00:19,110
...we don't feel like we have the energy.

9
00:00:19,160 --> 00:00:20,310
Plus, we don't think it's fair

10
00:00:20,360 --> 00:00:22,710
that every year the burden falls on us.

11
00:00:23,730 --> 00:00:25,670
That doesn't sound like you.

12
00:00:27,160 --> 00:00:29,140
That's Monica talking.

13
00:00:30,340 --> 00:00:33,800
No, no, we made this decision together.

14
00:00:33,850 --> 00:00:35,880
She's putting words in your mouth.

15
00:00:36,290 --> 00:00:37,990
Don't you put words in people's mouths.

16
00:00:38,040 --> 00:00:39,800
You put turkey in people's mouths.

17
00:00:41,120 --> 00:00:42,330
I can't believe this.

18
00:00:42,380 --> 00:00:44,480
This is Emma's first Thanksgiving.

19
00:00:44,610 --> 00:00:45,850
No, it's not.

20
00:00:45,900 --> 00:00:48,190
It's not? When was she born?

21
00:00:50,470 --> 00:00:51,490
Well, personally,

22
00:00:51,540 --> 00:00:53,660
I think it's great you're giving yourself a break.

23
00:00:53,710 --> 00:00:55,060
Thank you, Pheebs.

24
00:00:55,110 --> 00:00:56,500
Sure. It's just as well.

25
00:00:56,650 --> 00:00:58,120
I mean, last year wasn't very good.

26
00:00:58,170 --> 00:00:59,780
I think she's losing her touch.

27
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:03,390
What? You are way off, lady.

28
00:01:03,440 --> 00:01:04,970
Am l? Really? Am l?

29
00:01:05,020 --> 00:01:06,890
Well, why don't you cook Thanksgiving dinner

30
00:01:06,940 --> 00:01:08,190
and prove me wrong.

31
00:01:09,700 --> 00:01:11,340
Well, think about it.

32
00:01:11,390 --> 00:01:13,550
You'd be trying to top what you did last year.

33
00:01:13,600 --> 00:01:16,320
You'd be in competition with yourself.

34
00:01:18,110 --> 00:01:19,540
That's my favorite kind.

35
00:01:20,430 --> 00:01:22,480
Okay, we are doing this.

36
00:01:22,870 --> 00:01:25,290
Don't let yourself get manipulated this way.

37
00:01:25,340 --> 00:01:26,690
Stay out of this, Chandler.

38
00:01:26,740 --> 00:01:28,830
This is between me and me.

39
00:01:30,520 --> 00:01:31,680
We are supposed to

40
00:01:31,730 --> 00:01:33,270
make these decisions together.

41
00:01:34,490 --> 00:01:36,910
Dr. Phi:一档帮人解决家庭问题的脱口秀

42
00:01:34,490 --> 00:01:36,910
Did you not watch the <i>Dr. Phil</i> I taped for you?

43
00:01:39,180 --> 00:01:41,420
《老友记》第十季第八集 感恩节晚餐大家都迟到了

44
00:02:31,760 --> 00:02:33,810
- Hey. - Hi. Happy Thanksgiving.

45
00:02:33,860 --> 00:02:36,330
Happy Needless Turkey-Murder Day.

46
00:02:37,850 --> 00:02:39,560
You guys, I ordered some chocolate pies

47
00:02:39,610 --> 00:02:41,140
from that bakery on Bleeker.

48
00:02:41,190 --> 00:02:42,190
Could you pick them up for me?

49
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:44,000
You're not making the pies?

50
00:02:44,050 --> 00:02:45,500
I don't make chocolate pies.

51
00:02:45,550 --> 00:02:46,450
When I was younger,

52
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:48,610
I entered this pie-eating contest.

53
00:02:48,660 --> 00:02:49,650
I ate so many

54
00:02:49,700 --> 00:02:51,350
that the thought of them makes me sick.

55
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:53,230
Did you at least win the contest?

56
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:56,180
Two minutes, twelve pies and a part of one tin.

57
00:02:57,560 --> 00:02:58,880
Okay, I'll see you guys at 4.

58
00:02:58,930 --> 00:02:59,940
Can't wait.

59
00:02:59,990 --> 00:03:02,320
This dinner is gonna be so great.

60
00:03:02,370 --> 00:03:04,580
In your face, last-year me.

61
00:03:06,570 --> 00:03:07,630
- Hey, Rach? - Yeah.

62
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:09,190
What's Emma doing today?

63
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:10,810
Well, let's see,

64
00:03:10,860 --> 00:03:13,700
I know that she has a meeting with her lawyer...

65
00:03:13,750 --> 00:03:16,510
...and then she has to make a very big poop.

66
00:03:18,460 --> 00:03:19,330
Why?

67
00:03:19,380 --> 00:03:21,920
Well, I want to enter her in a baby pageant.

68
00:03:21,970 --> 00:03:23,250
Oh, my God.

69
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:25,730
That's the creepiest thing I've ever heard.

70
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:28,190
Okay, but before you say no,

71
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:30,150
my friend Suzanne is entering her kid.

72
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:31,040
And compared to Emma,

73
00:03:31,090 --> 00:03:32,730
she's a real dog.

74
00:03:33,330 --> 00:03:35,760
Phoebe, all babies are beautiful.

75
00:03:35,810 --> 00:03:36,630
Oh, okay.

76
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:38,330
No. Phoebe,

77
00:03:38,380 --> 00:03:41,340
just the idea of pitting one baby against another...

78
00:03:41,390 --> 00:03:42,590
...l mean, you know,

79
00:03:42,640 --> 00:03:44,630
and judging who's cuter just for a trophy...

80
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:45,700
And a thousand dollars.

81
00:03:45,750 --> 00:03:48,670
...is something I'm very interested in.

82
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:52,380
Oh, please, do not tell Ross.

83
00:03:52,430 --> 00:03:53,390
He still believes that

84
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:55,200
what's on the inside is important.

85
00:03:55,250 --> 00:03:58,280
Okay. And Emma needs a cowgirl outfit

86
00:03:58,330 --> 00:03:59,480
for the competition.

87
00:03:59,530 --> 00:04:02,240
Where am I gonna get a cowgirl outfit on Thanksgiving?

88
00:04:02,290 --> 00:04:03,510
Well, I was thinking--

89
00:04:03,560 --> 00:04:06,070
Take the clothes off Joey's Cabbage Patch Kid!

90
00:04:16,050 --> 00:04:17,900
Did someone drop the baton again?

91
00:04:17,950 --> 00:04:19,880
Why come all the way from Kansas

92
00:04:19,930 --> 00:04:20,980
to do that?

93
00:04:24,190 --> 00:04:26,770
I don't get older, I just get better.

94
00:04:28,100 --> 00:04:29,730
You know what just occurred to me?

95
00:04:29,780 --> 00:04:31,300
This could be our last Thanksgiving

96
00:04:31,350 --> 00:04:32,530
just the two of us.

97
00:04:32,580 --> 00:04:34,860
I mean, we could be getting a baby soon.

98
00:04:34,910 --> 00:04:35,770
You don't know that.

99
00:04:35,820 --> 00:04:37,440
Somebody's gonna pick us.

100
00:04:37,490 --> 00:04:38,580
But we haven't heard a thing

101
00:04:38,630 --> 00:04:40,400
from the adoption agency.

102
00:04:40,450 --> 00:04:42,590
I'm telling you, it's gonna happen.

103
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:43,600
Next year,

104
00:04:43,650 --> 00:04:46,570
it's gonna be you, me and little Hemingway Bing.

105
00:04:48,610 --> 00:04:50,260
What? He's my favorite author.

106
00:04:50,310 --> 00:04:51,660
Name one of his books.

107
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,670
<i>The Firm</i>?

108
00:05:00,630 --> 00:05:03,150
Okay, let's see. Okay, the turkey's in the oven.

109
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:04,390
The stuffing is ready.

110
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:04,940
You know,

111
00:05:04,990 --> 00:05:07,180
you always cook this meal all by yourself.

112
00:05:07,230 --> 00:05:08,590
Let me help this year.

113
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:10,330
Oh, Chandler, that's sweet.

114
00:05:10,380 --> 00:05:13,160
But you don't have to do everything Dr. Phil tells you to do.

115
00:05:14,130 --> 00:05:16,170
I'm serious, let me do something.

116
00:05:16,220 --> 00:05:19,270
Just not the turkey. Nothing high-profile.

117
00:05:19,760 --> 00:05:21,040
Okay, let's see.

118
00:05:21,090 --> 00:05:22,670
Oh, the cranberry sauce.

119
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:23,510
It's easy to make,

120
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:25,170
and no one really cares about it.

121
00:05:26,530 --> 00:05:27,510
Tell me more.

122
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:30,300
I'm gonna go check on something across the hall.

123
00:05:30,350 --> 00:05:32,080
You start by washing these.

124
00:05:34,620 --> 00:05:35,980
Not with soap!

125
00:05:40,060 --> 00:05:43,720
You obviously haven't tasted my Palmolive potatoes.

126
00:05:45,850 --> 00:05:47,670
Hi. Hey, guess what Joey has.

127
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:49,700
Three tickets to today's Rangers game!

128
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:51,670
Dude, I wanted him to guess.

129
00:05:52,660 --> 00:05:53,680
Oh, my God.

130
00:05:53,730 --> 00:05:55,420
Yeah, they're great seats too.

131
00:05:55,470 --> 00:05:56,260
Guess where they are.

132
00:05:56,310 --> 00:05:57,160
Center ice.

133
00:05:59,380 --> 00:06:01,440
Did I do something to you?

134
00:06:03,790 --> 00:06:05,190
The game's at 1.

135
00:06:05,190 --> 00:06:05,880
So?

136
00:06:05,930 --> 00:06:07,660
Dinner's at 4. We'll never make it back.

137
00:06:07,710 --> 00:06:08,950
So we'll leave before it's over.

138
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:09,770
We'll be back in time.

139
00:06:09,820 --> 00:06:10,620
You said that now.

140
00:06:10,670 --> 00:06:12,880
But it could take us a long time to get back home.

141
00:06:12,930 --> 00:06:14,220
Plus, Joey could get lost

142
00:06:14,270 --> 00:06:16,540
and they could have to page us to go pick him up.

143
00:06:18,220 --> 00:06:20,310
Dude, two times that happened!

144
00:06:22,020 --> 00:06:24,410
Look, Monica's been working hard all day.

145
00:06:24,460 --> 00:06:26,290
She didn't want to host in the first place.

146
00:06:26,340 --> 00:06:27,370
We shouldn't go.

147
00:06:27,510 --> 00:06:28,870
He's right, man.

148
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:31,190
Yeah, I guess. So we'll see you at 4.

149
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:31,810
Okay.

150
00:06:31,860 --> 00:06:32,950
And get ready to taste

151
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,820
my very special cranberries.

152
00:06:35,310 --> 00:06:38,370
Or should I say "Chan-berries"?

153
00:06:42,410 --> 00:06:44,310
That's some gentle comedy, dude.

154
00:06:46,180 --> 00:06:47,920
We're still going to the game, right?

155
00:06:47,970 --> 00:06:48,720
Yeah.

156
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:58,260
Hey.

157
00:06:58,310 --> 00:06:59,970
Phoebe, listen, I think we gotta go.

158
00:07:00,020 --> 00:07:01,550
This place is freaking me out.

159
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:03,010
I've been watching this guy over there.

160
00:07:03,060 --> 00:07:04,670
I don't think he came with a kid.

161
00:07:05,670 --> 00:07:07,250
But we can't leave now.

162
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:08,800
There was this one baby, Haley,

163
00:07:08,850 --> 00:07:09,720
who was favored to win...

164
00:07:09,770 --> 00:07:11,870
...she got croup, so she had to stay home.

165
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:14,650
This competition just blew wide-open, folks.

166
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:17,650
Phoebe, it's just too weird.

167
00:07:17,700 --> 00:07:20,330
I just saw a 1 -year-old with pantyhose on.

168
00:07:20,380 --> 00:07:22,750
Oh, I know. We should've been more prepared.

169
00:07:24,650 --> 00:07:26,420
It's okay. Now, the way I see it,

170
00:07:26,470 --> 00:07:28,910
our real competition now is Cameron.

171
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:30,950
My God, they just took her sweater off.

172
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:33,130
Michelin Man:著名轮胎的卡通形象

173
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:33,130
Look at those arms. Hello, Michelin Man.

174
00:07:33,180 --> 00:07:35,520
Phoebe, come on.

175
00:07:35,570 --> 00:07:37,350
You know what, it's already 3:00.

176
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:39,040
They haven't even gotten to Emma's group yet.

177
00:07:39,090 --> 00:07:40,490
We got dinner.

178
00:07:40,540 --> 00:07:41,980
But Emma's got what it takes.

179
00:07:42,030 --> 00:07:43,260
She could go all the way!

180
00:07:45,810 --> 00:07:48,100
Phoebe, you have to calm down.

181
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:49,520
Okay.

182
00:07:49,900 --> 00:07:53,200
Rachel, the hottest babies in the tri-state area

183
00:07:53,250 --> 00:07:55,580
are in this room right now.

184
00:07:57,290 --> 00:07:58,980
I overheard a judge say

185
00:07:59,030 --> 00:08:01,020
that not one of them holds a candle to Emma.

186
00:08:01,330 --> 00:08:02,790
- Really? - Yeah.

187
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:04,460
You heard him say that?

188
00:08:04,510 --> 00:08:05,250
Yeah.

189
00:08:05,750 --> 00:08:07,840
All right. Okay. All right,

190
00:08:07,890 --> 00:08:10,060
let's give these babies something to cry about.

191
00:08:10,110 --> 00:08:12,740
Good. Let's get down to business.

192
00:08:12,790 --> 00:08:13,970
Emma needs some makeup.

193
00:08:14,020 --> 00:08:15,100
What?

194
00:08:15,150 --> 00:08:17,810
She's gonna look washed-out next to the others.

195
00:08:17,860 --> 00:08:20,260
No, Phoebe, I'm not letting you put makeup on my baby.

196
00:08:20,310 --> 00:08:21,030
Why not?

197
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:22,450
Because I already did.

198
00:08:29,560 --> 00:08:33,520
You suck! Get off the ice, you idiot!

199
00:08:34,530 --> 00:08:36,750
- What a game. - I know. Yeah.

200
00:08:37,370 --> 00:08:39,240
I can't believe Chandler's missing this.

201
00:08:39,290 --> 00:08:40,610
I'm sorry he's not here.

202
00:08:40,660 --> 00:08:41,550
But I gotta say,

203
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:43,990
I am really enjoying nacho chair.

204
00:08:45,090 --> 00:08:46,680
Yeah, I'd probably enjoy it more

205
00:08:46,730 --> 00:08:48,640
if you didn't keep batting my hand away.

206
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,820
These seats are great.

207
00:08:52,870 --> 00:08:53,820
I know, I know.

208
00:08:53,870 --> 00:08:56,100
When I was here for "Holidays on lce" ...

209
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:59,090
...l was sitting so far away,

210
00:08:59,140 --> 00:09:01,510
Michelle Kwan couldn't read my banner.

211
00:08:59,140 --> 00:09:01,510
Michelle Kwan:花样滑冰世界冠军

212
00:09:02,740 --> 00:09:04,050
We'd better get going.

213
00:09:04,050 --> 00:09:05,480
If we don't leave now, we're gonna be late.

214
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:07,130
But it's a tie game.

215
00:09:07,180 --> 00:09:08,510
So we're a little late.

216
00:09:08,560 --> 00:09:09,930
The girls will be there.

217
00:09:09,980 --> 00:09:12,060
Let's just stay for one more goal.

218
00:09:12,110 --> 00:09:13,730
- I don't know. - One more fight.

219
00:09:13,780 --> 00:09:14,990
- Okay. - Okay.

220
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:20,650
Where is everybody?

221
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:21,860
They're 45 minutes late.

222
00:09:21,910 --> 00:09:23,540
I can't believe they're not here.

223
00:09:23,590 --> 00:09:26,050
I slave and I slave for what?

224
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:29,290
They've ruined Cranberry Day.

225
00:09:31,540 --> 00:09:32,890
How late are we?

226
00:09:32,890 --> 00:09:33,730
Forty-five minutes.

227
00:09:33,780 --> 00:09:36,080
- Here. - Okay.

228
00:09:36,870 --> 00:09:38,670
Rachel and Phoebe are already there,

229
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:39,920
so they probably started without us.

230
00:09:39,970 --> 00:09:41,260
We could just slip in,

231
00:09:41,310 --> 00:09:42,730
and no one needs to know where we were.

232
00:09:44,730 --> 00:09:47,220
You may want to lose the foam finger.

233
00:09:47,270 --> 00:09:49,180
Oh, no, no, no.

234
00:09:49,230 --> 00:09:50,930
You just want to put it on your hand.

235
00:09:54,770 --> 00:09:56,860
You're not at Thanksgiving?

236
00:09:56,910 --> 00:09:58,600
No, we're late.

237
00:09:58,650 --> 00:10:00,180
What are you doing here?

238
00:10:00,230 --> 00:10:01,620
We're late too.

239
00:10:02,410 --> 00:10:03,580
We figured we could be late

240
00:10:03,630 --> 00:10:05,200
because you'd be on time.

241
00:10:05,250 --> 00:10:07,460
Don't point that thing at me, Tribbiani.

242
00:10:08,340 --> 00:10:09,930
So nobody's here?

243
00:10:09,980 --> 00:10:11,290
Monica's gonna kill us.

244
00:10:11,340 --> 00:10:12,520
Yeah, where were you?

245
00:10:12,570 --> 00:10:14,550
Yeah, what's with the trophy?

246
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:17,560
Well, we were at a spelling bee.

247
00:10:19,290 --> 00:10:20,640
And I won.

248
00:10:21,870 --> 00:10:23,440
You won an adult

249
00:10:23,490 --> 00:10:26,050
Thanksgiving Day spelling bee?

250
00:10:26,570 --> 00:10:29,300
Yes. Y-E-S. Yes.

251
00:10:29,810 --> 00:10:31,700
Let me see this.

252
00:10:31,930 --> 00:10:35,390
"Grand Supreme Little Darling, New York Division"?

253
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:36,810
That's me.

254
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:41,720
You entered Emma in a beauty pageant?

255
00:10:42,510 --> 00:10:45,790
And it looks like she put makeup on her.

256
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:48,320
Wait a second...

257
00:10:48,370 --> 00:10:51,080
Where have I seen that cowgirl outfit before?

258
00:10:52,220 --> 00:10:53,490
I can't believe this.

259
00:10:53,540 --> 00:10:54,750
She's our daughter.

260
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:57,400
That you would treat her like some kind of show dog

261
00:10:57,450 --> 00:10:58,630
is inexcusable.

262
00:10:58,680 --> 00:11:00,220
She won a thousand dollars.

263
00:11:00,270 --> 00:11:02,580
So this is an annual thing?

264
00:11:06,370 --> 00:11:08,640
That's Alicia May Emory's outfit!

265
00:11:10,510 --> 00:11:12,130
Guys, there are people in there

266
00:11:12,180 --> 00:11:13,620
who are not getting any happier.

267
00:11:13,740 --> 00:11:14,960
What are we gonna do?

268
00:11:15,010 --> 00:11:16,140
I don't know, you guys figure it out.

269
00:11:16,190 --> 00:11:17,370
I gotta put Emma down for a nap.

270
00:11:17,420 --> 00:11:18,830
And, Rach, while you're in there,

271
00:11:18,830 --> 00:11:20,380
throw something on Alicia May.

